  84. ‌    type 'a t =
  85.       { mutable size: int;                  (* number of entries *)
  86.         mutable data: 'a bucketlist array;  (* the buckets *)
  87.         seed: int;                          (* for randomization *)
  88.         initial_size: int;                  (* initial array size *)
  89.       }

  91. ‌    and 'a bucketlist =
  92.     | Empty
  93.     | Cons of int (* hash of the key *) * 'a H.container * 'a bucketlist

  95.     (** the hash of the key is kept in order to test the equality of the hash
  96.       before the key. Same reason as for Weak.Make *)

  98. ‌    type key = H.t

  100. ‌    let rec power_2_above x n =
  101.       if x >= n then x
  102.       else if x * 2 > Sys.max_array_length then x
  103.       else power_2_above (x * 2) n

  105. ‌    let prng = lazy (Random.State.make_self_init())

  107. ‌    let create ?(random = (Hashtbl.is_randomized ())) initial_size =
  108.       let s = power_2_above 16 initial_size in
  109.       let seed = if random then Random.State.bits (Lazy.force prng) else 0 in
  110.       { initial_size = s; size = 0; seed = seed; data = Array.make s Empty }

  112. ‌    let clear h =
  113.       h.size <- 0;
  114.       let len = Array.length h.data in
  115.       for i = 0 to len - 1 do
  116.         h.data.(i) <- Empty
  117.       done

  119. ‌    let reset h =
  120.       let len = Array.length h.data in
  121.       if len = h.initial_size then
  122.         clear h
  123.       else begin
  124.         h.size <- 0;
  125.         h.data <- Array.make h.initial_size Empty
  126.       end

  128.     let copy h = { h with data = Array.copy h.data }

  130.     let key_index h hkey =
  131.       hkey land (Array.length h.data - 1)

  133.     let clean h =
  134.       let rec do_bucket = function
  135.         | Empty ->
  136.             Empty
  137.         | Cons(_, c, rest) when not (H.check_key c) ->
  138.             h.size <- h.size - 1;
  139.             do_bucket rest
  140.         | Cons(hkey, c, rest) ->
  141.             Cons(hkey, c, do_bucket rest)
  142.       in
  143.       let d = h.data in
  144.       for i = 0 to Array.length d - 1 do
  145.         d.(i) <- do_bucket d.(i)
  146.       done

  148.     (** resize is the only function to do the actual cleaning of dead keys
  149.         (remove does it just because it could).

  151.         The goal is to:

  153.         - not resize infinitely when the actual number of alive keys is
  154.         bounded but keys are continuously added. That would happen if
  155.         this function always resize.
  156.         - not call this function after each addition, that would happen if this
  157.         function don't resize even when only one key is dead.

  159.         So the algorithm:
  160.         - clean the keys before resizing
  161.         - if the number of remaining keys is less than half the size of the
  162.         array, don't resize.
  163.         - if it is more, resize.

  165.         The second problem remains if the table reaches {!Sys.max_array_length}.

  167.     *)
  168.     let resize h =
  169.       let odata = h.data in
  170.       let osize = Array.length odata in
  171.       let nsize = osize * 2 in
  172.       clean h;
  173.       if nsize < Sys.max_array_length && h.size >= osize lsr 1 then begin
  174.         let ndata = Array.make nsize Empty in
  175.         h.data <- ndata;       (* so that key_index sees the new bucket count *)
  176.         let rec insert_bucket = function
  177.             Empty -> ()
  178.           | Cons(hkey, data, rest) ->
  179.               insert_bucket rest; (* preserve original order of elements *)
  180.               let nidx = key_index h hkey in
  181.               ndata.(nidx) <- Cons(hkey, data, ndata.(nidx)) in
  182.         for i = 0 to osize - 1 do
  183.           insert_bucket odata.(i)
  184.         done
  185.       end

  187. ‌    let add h key info =
  188.       let hkey = H.seeded_hash h.seed key in
  189.       let i = key_index h hkey in
  190.       let container = H.create key info in
  191.       let bucket = Cons(hkey, container, h.data.(i)) in
  192.       h.data.(i) <- bucket;
  193.       h.size <- h.size + 1;
  194.       if h.size > Array.length h.data lsl 1 then resize h

  196. ‌    let remove h key =
  197.       let hkey = H.seeded_hash h.seed key in
  198.       let rec remove_bucket = function
  199.         | Empty -> Empty
  200.         | Cons(hk, c, next) when hkey = hk ->
  201.             begin match H.equal c key with
  202.             | ETrue -> h.size <- h.size - 1; next
  203.             | EFalse -> Cons(hk, c, remove_bucket next)
  204.             | EDead ->
  205.                 (* The dead key is automatically removed. It is acceptable
  206.                     for this function since it already removes a binding *)
  207.                 h.size <- h.size - 1;
  208.                 remove_bucket next
  209.             end
  210.         | Cons(hk,c,next) -> Cons(hk, c, remove_bucket next) in
  211.       let i = key_index h hkey in
  212.       h.data.(i) <- remove_bucket h.data.(i)

  214.     (** {!find} don't remove dead keys because it would be surprising for
  215.         the user that a read-only function mutates the state (eg. concurrent
  216.         access). Same for {!mem}.
  217.     *)
  218. ‌    let rec find_rec key hkey = function
  219.       | Empty ->
  220.           raise Not_found
  221.       | Cons(hk, c, rest) when hkey = hk  ->
  222.           begin match H.equal c key with
  223.           | ETrue ->
  224.               begin match H.get_data c with
  225.               | None ->
  226.                   (* This case is not impossible because the gc can run between
  227.                       H.equal and H.get_data *)
  228.                   find_rec key hkey rest
  229.               | Some d -> d
  230.               end
  231.           | EFalse -> find_rec key hkey rest
  232.           | EDead ->
  233.               find_rec key hkey rest
  234.           end
  235.       | Cons(_, _, rest) ->
  236.           find_rec key hkey rest

  238. ‌    let find h key =
  239.       let hkey = H.seeded_hash h.seed key in
  240.       (* TODO inline 3 iterations *)
  241.       find_rec key hkey (h.data.(key_index h hkey))

  243. ‌    let rec find_rec_opt key hkey = function
  244.       | Empty ->
  245.           None
  246.       | Cons(hk, c, rest) when hkey = hk  ->
  247.           begin match H.equal c key with
  248.           | ETrue ->
  249.               begin match H.get_data c with
  250.               | None ->
  251.                   (* This case is not impossible because the gc can run between
  252.                       H.equal and H.get_data *)
  253.                   find_rec_opt key hkey rest
  254.               | Some _ as d -> d
  255.               end
  256.           | EFalse -> find_rec_opt key hkey rest
  257.           | EDead ->
  258.               find_rec_opt key hkey rest
  259.           end
  260.       | Cons(_, _, rest) ->
  261.           find_rec_opt key hkey rest

  263. ‌    let find_opt h key =

  268. ‌    let find_all h key =
  269.       let hkey = H.seeded_hash h.seed key in
  270.       let rec find_in_bucket = function
  271.       | Empty -> []
  272.       | Cons(hk, c, rest) when hkey = hk  ->
  273.           begin match H.equal c key with
  274.           | ETrue -> begin match H.get_data c with
  275.               | None ->
  276.                   find_in_bucket rest
  277.               | Some d -> d::find_in_bucket rest
  278.             end
  279.           | EFalse -> find_in_bucket rest
  280.           | EDead ->
  281.               find_in_bucket rest
  282.           end
  283.       | Cons(_, _, rest) ->
  284.           find_in_bucket rest in
  285.       find_in_bucket h.data.(key_index h hkey)


  288. ‌    let replace h key info =
  289.       let hkey = H.seeded_hash h.seed key in
  290.       let rec replace_bucket = function
  291.         | Empty -> raise Not_found
  292.         | Cons(hk, c, next) when hkey = hk ->
  293.             begin match H.equal c key with
  294.             | ETrue -> H.set_key_data c key info
  295.             | EFalse | EDead -> replace_bucket next
  296.             end
  297.         | Cons(_,_,next) -> replace_bucket next
  298.       in
  299.       let i = key_index h hkey in
  300.       let l = h.data.(i) in
  301.       try
  302.         replace_bucket l
  303.       with Not_found ->
  304.         let container = H.create key info in
  305.         h.data.(i) <- Cons(hkey, container, l);
  306.         h.size <- h.size + 1;
  307.         if h.size > Array.length h.data lsl 1 then resize h

  309. ‌    let mem h key =
  310.       let hkey = H.seeded_hash h.seed key in
  311.       let rec mem_in_bucket = function
  312.       | Empty ->
  313.           false
  314.       | Cons(hk, c, rest) when hk = hkey ->
  315.           begin match H.equal c key with
  316.           | ETrue -> true
  317.           | EFalse | EDead -> mem_in_bucket rest
  318.           end
  319.       | Cons(_hk, _c, rest) -> mem_in_bucket rest in
  320.       mem_in_bucket h.data.(key_index h hkey)

  322. ‌    let length h = h.size

  324. ‌    let rec bucket_length accu = function
  325.       | Empty -> accu
  326.       | Cons(_, _, rest) -> bucket_length (accu + 1) rest

  328. ‌    let stats h =
  329.       let mbl =
  330.         Array.fold_left (fun m b -> Int.max m (bucket_length 0 b)) 0 h.data in
  331.       let histo = Array.make (mbl + 1) 0 in
  332.       Array.iter
  333.         (fun b ->
  334.            let l = bucket_length 0 b in
  335.            histo.(l) <- histo.(l) + 1)
  336.         h.data;
  337.       { Hashtbl.num_bindings = h.size;
  338.         num_buckets = Array.length h.data;
  339.         max_bucket_length = mbl;
  340.         bucket_histogram = histo }

  342.     let rec bucket_length_alive accu = function
  343.       | Empty -> accu
  344.       | Cons(_, c, rest) when H.check_key c ->
  345.           bucket_length_alive (accu + 1) rest
  346.       | Cons(_, _, rest) -> bucket_length_alive accu rest

  348. ‌    let stats_alive h =
  349.       let size = ref 0 in
  350.       let mbl =
  351.         Array.fold_left
  352.           (fun m b -> Int.max m (bucket_length_alive 0 b)) 0 h.data
  353.       in
  354.       let histo = Array.make (mbl + 1) 0 in
  355.       Array.iter
  356.         (fun b ->
  357.            let l = bucket_length_alive 0 b in
  358.            size := !size + l;
  359.            histo.(l) <- histo.(l) + 1)
  360.         h.data;
  361.       { Hashtbl.num_bindings = !size;
  362.         num_buckets = Array.length h.data;
  363.         max_bucket_length = mbl;
  364.         bucket_histogram = histo }

  366.     let add_seq tbl i =
  367.       Seq.iter (fun (k,v) -> add tbl k v) i

  369.     let replace_seq tbl i =
  370.       Seq.iter (fun (k,v) -> replace tbl k v) i

  372.     let of_seq i =
  373.       let tbl = create 16 in
  374.       replace_seq tbl i;
  375.       tbl

  377.   end
  378. end

  404.   let make key data =

  406.     set_data eph data;
  407.     set_key eph key;
  408.     eph

  410.   let query eph key =
  411.     match get_key eph with
  412.     | None -> None
  413.     | Some k when k == key -> get_data eph
  414.     | Some _ -> None

  416.   module MakeSeeded (H:Hashtbl.SeededHashedType) =

  455.   module Bucket = struct

  457.     type nonrec ('k, 'd) t = ('k, 'd) t list ref
  458.     let k1_make = make
  459.     let make () = ref []
  460.     let add b k d = b := k1_make k d :: !b

  462.     let test_key k e =
  463.       match get_key e with
  464.       | Some x when x == k -> true
  465.       | _ -> false

  467.     let remove b k =
  468.       let rec loop l acc =
  469.         match l with
  470.         | [] -> ()
  471.         | h :: t when test_key k h -> b := List.rev_append acc t
  472.         | h :: t -> loop t (h :: acc)
  473.       in
  474.       loop !b []

  476.     let find b k =
  477.       match List.find_opt (test_key k) !b with
  478.       | Some e -> get_data e
  479.       | None -> None

  481.     let length b = List.length !b
  482.     let clear b = b := []

  484.   end

  486. end

  643.   module MakeSeeded (H:Hashtbl.SeededHashedType) =
  644.     GenHashTable.MakeSeeded(struct

  662.         let len' = length c in

  664.         else
  665.           let rec equal_array k c i =
  666.             if i < 0 then GenHashTable.ETrue

  669.               | None -> GenHashTable.EDead
  670.               | Some ki ->

  673.                   else GenHashTable.EFalse

  675.           equal_array k c (len-1)
  676.       let get_data = get_data
  677.       let set_key_data c k d =
  678.         unset_data c;

  680.           set_key c i k.(i);
  681.         done;

  684.         let rec check c i =
  685.           i < 0 || (check_key c i && check c (i-1)) in
  686.         check c (length c - 1)
  687.     end)
